&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you enthusiastic and keen to work with children and young people across the age ranges?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Sirona care &amp; health Community Paediatric and Community Paediatric Therapies Teams are looking for an experienced and highly skilled Clinical Psychologist to work as part of a virtual team, delivering the services autism diagnostic pathway (SCAMP-Social Communication Autism, Multi-Professional Pathway)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have 20 hours a week to offer, with some flexibility around which days you would work. Your role will include facilitating all aspects of the SCAMP Pathway (managing referrals, completing diagnostic assessments and being the lead clinician at the end of the pathway. &lt;br /&gt;Everyday is different and you need to be able to prioritise, work on your own initiative and be flexible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal discussion or visits by arrangement are encouraged to fully explain the role. Please contact Alyson Harris, Therapies Manager or Rosie Grenter, Lead Nurse, Community Paediatric Team on 01934 881306 for more information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
